 <span class="hero__eyebrow">About CoreFlow</span>
 <h1 class="hero__title">Infusion care that puts value first.</h1>
 <p class="hero__lead">CoreFlow Specialty Infusion exists because home infusion in South Carolina needed a different model. One that measures success by what prescribers, patients, and payers actually receive, not by what a pharmacy provides.</p>
 </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
 <div class="container">
 <p class="lead">We are a non-compounding, non-retail specialty infusion pharmacy. We receive commercially manufactured medications, maintain them under pharmaceutical-grade cold chain conditions, and dispatch credentialed registered nurses to patient homes for administration. That's our model. It's specific by design.</p>
 <h2 class="section-title mt-6">Why we built CoreFlow.</h2>
 <p>Prescribers referring home infusion patients have historically faced the same set of problems: poor communication from pharmacy partners, inconsistent nursing quality, and referral processes that create more work than they eliminate.</p>
 <p>CoreFlow was built to solve those problems specifically. Not to be a retail pharmacy, not to be a staffing agency, and not to be a compounding operation. We do one thing: specialty infusion in the home, done well, right where you live.</p>
 <p>Our structure is intentional. Credentialed, supervised nurses. Pre-manufactured medications, not compounded. Local, not a national footprint that treats your community as a market segment.</p>
 <p>Too much of home infusion has become mail-order and PBM-driven. With medicine shipped in from another state, with no one local accountable for how it goes. We built the opposite: local nurses, a named clinical team, and communication that closes the loop every time.</p>
 <p>That commitment is part of why MUSC Health trusts CoreFlow as a home infusion partner and why we hold ourselves to the standards a health system of that caliber expects.</p>
 <p>CoreFlow was established as a joint venture with Council Capital, a healthcare-focused private equity firm. </p>
 </div>
</section>

